The paper deals with reducing feedback load in a multiuser MIMO downlink channel, which involves information theory (cs.IT), networking and communications (cs.NI), signal processing (cs.SI), and machine learning (cs.MM) techniques. The proposed scheme also involves decision thresholds and optimization, which are related to learning and generalization (cs.LG).
